Reasoning: The paper deals with the derivation of analytic expressions and bounds for special functions that are useful in wireless communication theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of communication systems. The sub-category cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely, as it deals with the design and analysis of communication networks. The sub-category cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is relevant as the paper involves extensive numerical comparisons. The sub-category cs.SI (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with the performance evaluation of communication systems. Finally, the sub-category cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is relevant as the paper involves the development of mathematical tools for communication theory.
